<SLUG> BC-GLF-SKINNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
O'MEARA TO CUT BACK, DUVAL TO PICK IT UP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LARRY MORGAN  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INDIO, Calif. _ Expect to see less of Mark O'Meara and more of
David Duval on next year's PGA Tour.
</P>
<P>
   O'Meara, who had a difficult time living up to an impressive
1998 season that included two major championships (British Open and
Masters), will cut back his early 2000 schedule in hopes of having
a stronger finish later in the year.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a fickle game, and sometimes you don't play as well as
you would like to,'' he said. ``Hopefully, next year, I can get it
straightened out. I'll play more in the states and not so much
overseas.''
</P>
<P>
   Duval, on the other hand, had a great start _ including his
final-round 59 at the Bob Hope Classic _ but began to fade in the
summer. He said he still will participate in most of the West Coast
tournaments but plans to play more as the year goes on in hopes of
staying sharp.
</P>
<P>
   ``After the U.S. Open, I never caught a good rhythm,'' he said.
``I don't think my game was a whole lot weaker, but I didn't give
myself opportunities to build on anything from one week to the
next. I believe that's why I didn't win any golf tournaments at the
end of the year.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know exactly what to do, but it looks like I'm going
to have to play more in the summer months.''
</P>
<P>
   Young blood: Sergio Garcia is the youngest competitor in Skins
Game history.
</P>
<P>
   He's 19 years, 10 months and 18 days old. Tiger Woods was 20
years, 10 months and 29 days old when he played in the '96 Skins
Game.
</P>
<P>
   Garcia, by the way, was born in January of 1980, the same month
Couples and O'Meara turned professional.
</P>
<P>
   Tennis anyone?: Garcia and Couples were thinking of playing some
tennis after Saturday's play.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sergio's pretty quick,'' O'Meara said. ``I saw him at the
Dunhill Cup, sprinting with Michael Jordan and beating him. Maybe
he can chase down some of Fred's half-volleys.''
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll play for some skins,'' Garcia joked.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
