<P>
   COVENT-GARDEN (London) _ It makes for a dull ending to a
long-running soap opera that once entertained with spats, insults,
scandals, brinkmanship and frequent warnings of imminent disaster.
But after four years of unremitting melodrama, the Royal Opera
House at Covent Garden has now completed a $360 million
redevelopment and will reopen on schedule on Dec. 1 with a gala of
song and dance attended by Queen Elizabeth. By Alan Riding.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-OFFICE-HITS (Hollywood) _ The five-day Thanksgiving weekend
movie box-office totals, paced by an astonishing $80.8 million
opening for ``Toy Story 2,'' might not have reached all the way to
infinity, but they were plenty strong enough shatter a host of
records and confirm Thanksgiving's position as an increasingly
important period to release new films. By Rick Lyman.
