war in the Persian Gulf. She commanded a military police unit that
helped keep the peace in Bosnia. The Army promoted her to colonel
two years ahead of schedule. But just as the odds were great that
she would be chosen for a star, Colonel Beard called it quits. At
the age of 45, after holding every job and attending every school
required to be selected as general, she decided she could no longer
dismiss the pull of her family.
