<P>
   SUDAN-USA (Washington) _ President Clinton is about to sign a
bill permitting the administration to pursue a contentious strategy
against the Islamic government in Sudan by giving food assistance
directly to rebels who have been fighting the authorities in
Khartoum for 16 years. By Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   TRADETALKS-PROTESTS (Seattle) _ In what is shaping up as one of
the biggest protest efforts in years, people from more than 500
organizations have poured into Seattle. They accuse the 134-nation
Geneva-based World Trade Organization, which is holding its
ministerial meeting here this week, of favoring free trade at the
expense of the environment, consumer safety, and workers' rights.
By Steven Greenhouse.
